quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
8,41,"Know that one fifth of the spoils that you obtain belongs to Allah, to the Messenger, to the near of kin, to the orphans, and the needy, and the wayfarer. {1} This you must observe if you truly believe In Allah and in what We sent down on Our servant {2} on the day when the true was distinguished from the false, the day on which the two armies met in battle. Allah has power over all things.",footnotes:1:This refers to the support and help from God which brought about victory for the Muslims.This verse lay's down the law for distributing the spoils of war. Spoils of war
8,42,"And recall when you were encamped at the nearer end of the valley (of Badr) and they were at the farther end and the caravan below you (along the seaside). Had you made a mutual appointment to meet in encounter, you would have declined. But encounter was brought about so that Allah might accomplish what He had decreed, and that he who was to perish should perish through a clear proof, and who was to survive might survive through a clear proof. {1} Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing. {2}",footnotes:1:The living and the dead spoken of in the above verse do not signify the individuals who survived the battle or those killed during it. The reference here is to the ideological entities of Islam and Jahiliyah.God is neither blind nor deaf nor ignorant. On the contrary
8,43,"And recall when Allah showed them to you in your dream to be few in number. {1} And had He showed them to you to be numerous, you would have flagged and disagreed with one another about fighting them. But Allah saved you. Surely Allah knows what is hidden in the breasts.",footnotes:1:This refers to the time when the Prophet (peace be on him) was leaving Madina along with the Muslims
8,44,"And recall when He made them appear as few in your eyes when you met them in the battle just as He lessened you in their eyes so that Allah might accomplish what had been decreed. To Allah are all matters referred for decision."
8,45,"Believers! When you encounter a host in battle, stand firm and remember Allah much that you may triumph."
